4. **Complexity**: The algorithm efficiently handles the problem with a time complexity of \(O(n^2 \log(\text{max coordinate}))\) due to nested loops and GCD computations, which is feasible for \(n \leq 500\). The space complexity is \(O(n^2)\) to store slope and midpoint groups.

